## 🗂️ Category 8: RESP Line Structure Correctness

> Verify generated RESP file has correct structure per spec.

### RESP-01 · RESP Approved Line — Units Distribution (PD)

- **Endpoint:** `POST /api/convert/mrx-to-resp`
- **Input:** Valid MRX (no deny/partial params)
- **Expected:** All Data lines have:
  - `MRx Claim Status == "PD"`
  - `Units approved == total units`
  - `Units Denied == 0`
- **Tags:** `functional`, `resp-structure`

### RESP-02 · RESP Denied Line — Units Cleared (DY)

- **Endpoint:** `POST /api/convert/mrx-to-resp`
- **Input:** Valid MRX · `denyPercentage=100`
- **Expected:** All eligible lines (units > 1) have:
  - `MRx Claim Status == "DY"`
  - `Units approved == 0`
  - `Units Denied == total units`
- **Tags:** `functional`, `resp-structure`, `deny`

### RESP-03 · RESP Partial Line — PA Split Constraint

- **Endpoint:** `POST /api/convert/mrx-to-resp`
- **Input:** Valid MRX · `partialPercentage=100`
- **Expected:** All eligible lines have:
  - `MRx Claim Status == "PA"`
  - `Units approved > Units Denied`
  - `Units approved > 0` AND `Units Denied > 0`
- **Tags:** `functional`, `resp-structure`, `partial`

### RESP-04 · Single-Unit Claims Never Denied

- **Endpoint:** `POST /api/convert/mrx-to-resp`
- **Input:** MRX file with single-unit claims · `denyPercentage=100`
- **Expected:** Single-unit data lines remain `"PD"` — never `"DY"` or `"PA"`
- **Tags:** `functional`, `resp-structure`, `business-rule`

